<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880219-0144 </DOCNO><HL> Boeing's British Airways Order </HL><SO> </SO><CO> BA BAB </CO><IN> ARO AIR </IN><DATELINE> SEATTLE  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Boeing Co. said British Airways ordered two 757 jetliners for a total of about $100 million, including spare parts.    The aerospace concern said the carrier will take delivery in the spring of 1989 and assign the planes to its newly formed Caledonian Airways charter operation.    Boeing, which has delivered or taken orders for 242 of the 757 twin-jet aircraft, said British Airways will be operating 36 of them after the latest two are delivered. </TEXT></DOC>